I REMEMBER THE STORY WAS ABOUT RONALD CLARK WHO GREW UP LIVING IN A CITY LIBRARY.
HIS FATHER WAS THE HEAD JANITOR SO THEY ALL LIVED ON THE TOP FLOOR RENT FREE
BECAUSE OF THIS RONALD ORIGINALL THOUGHT HIS FAMILY WAS RICH.
HIS FATHER THOUGHT THIS WAS FUNNY BECAUSE THEY WERE THE OPPOSITE.
HE DIDN'T CARE FOR LIVING AT THE LIBRARY AT FIRST AND WANTED TO HIDE IT FROM HIS CLASSMATES.
A LOT OF HIS CLASSMATES THOUGHT IT WAS AMUSING THAT RONALD WAS "THE KID THAT LIVES IN THE LIBRARY"
HIS FATHER TOOK GREAT PRIDE IN KEEPING THE LIBRARY CLEAN TO THE PUBLIC AND SPENT LOTS OF TIME WAXING TO KEEP EVERYTHING LOOKING NICE AND SHINY.
ANOTHER PLUS SIDE TO LIVING IN THE LIBRARY FOR LITTLE RONALD WAS THAT WHEN THE LIBRARY CLOSED, HE COULD RUN AROUND AND MAKE AS MUCH NOISE AS HE WANTED.
ONE OF RONALDS FAVORITE THINGS WAS IF HE EVER HAD ANY QUESTIONS ABOUT ANYTHING, HE COULD GO DOWNSTAIRS AND STAY UP UNTIL 3AM READING ABOUT WHATEVER HE WANTED

RONALD EVENTUALLY REALIZED HE WAS REALLY THANKFUL FOR LIVING IN THE LIBRARY BECAUSE IT OFFERED HIM THE OPPORTUNITY TO BE THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GO TO COLLEGE WHICH ALLOWED HIM TO BECOME A PROFESSOR.
I SAW A STORY ABOUT A BOY WHO WAS EMBARASSED ABOUT LIVING IN A LIBRARY
HIS DAD WAXED THE WHOLE PLACE
HE THOUGHT HE WAS RICH BECAUSE THEY LIVED IN THE LIBRARY BUT THEY WEREN'T
BECAUSE OF LIVING IN THE LIBRARY HE WAS ABLE TO GO TO COLLEGE AND BECOME A PROFESSOR
HIS FRIENDS THOUGHT IT WAS INTERESTING THAT HE LIVED IN THE LIBRARY
HE LIVED WITH HIS MOM AND DAD ON THE TOP FLOOR BECAUSE HIS DAD WAS A JANITOR
HE WAS THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GO TO COLLEGE
HE LOVED TO RUN AROUND THE LIBRARY AFTER HOURS
HE READ ABUT EVERYTHING HE COULD TO LEARN MORE
